DISCLOSURES
DISCLOSURES AND TERMS
Last updated May 14, 2018
Valuation Disclosures

Investment values presented on this dashboard represent estimates of current value prepared in accordance with the methodologies described below.

For early-stage companies, valuations are generally marked up or down to a company's latest priced round. Companies that do not have a new priced round since the last mark are held at the last mark or cost. Investments may also be marked down (but never up) at our discretion. This is an industry-standard method.

For later-stage companies, investments are sent to a third-party for valuation if the company is valued over $100M, the investment is estimated to be worth over $10M, and 24 months have passed since the last investment. Smaller investments in later-stage companies are valued using the same method as early-stage companies.

Confidentiality

It is important that you keep information about companies and valuation estimates presented on this dashboard confidential. Disclosure of any such information may constitute a breach of your obligations under the agreements relating to such investment and may violate AngelList's terms of service and you may no longer be able to invest via AngelList.
